article.headline: Air Force 70, TCU 65
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Michael Lyons scored 20 points and Air Force hit five free throws in the final 38.5 seconds for a 70-65 come-from-behind victory over Texas Christian on Wednesday night. After trailing 34-27 at the break, Air Force (15-13, 6-9 Mountain West) opened the second half with a 16-3 run. TCU's lead evaporated after the Horned Frogs (10-21, 1-15) went 5:47 without a basket early in the second half. TCU hit four 3-pointers to battle back and tie the game at 52-52 at the 7:47 mark, but Air Force responded with a 13-3 run to build a 10-point lead with 3:30 remaining. TCU would not go away, tying the game at 65-65 with 1:03 remaining on a layup by Hank Thorns. The Falcons then scored the next five points from the free throw line to seal the win. Greg Hill led TCU with a game-high 23 points.
